phrases: It is taking you too long to line the pins up with the shear line.
I am sorry I have to keep asking you to help me with this, Miss Dorothy.
Oh, it is not your fault.
Um, how did you do that?
They are just not cut out to be teachers.
I believe they are saying rude things about us.
I think it is fair to get angry.
Maybe we should go with something simpler.
You really like that song, do not you, Miss Dorothy?
You hum that tune all the time.
It is been planted inside the liaison's body.
And you want me to grab the liaison and remove the cipher?
He should be taken to the morgue in the next few days.
You want me to raid a corpse.
It is better than killing, I would say.
Numbers one and two on my list of least favorite spy jobs.
Do not tell me you want me to clean out every corpse in the morgue?
The Duke of Normandy has an accomplice there.
He knows who to look for.
I am supposed to be working Operation: Changeling.
Because that accomplice is someone with whom you are well acquainted.
Oh, it was just a cat.
Sorry to drag you along for this.
If anything happens, I will need someone to act as liaison.
They say half the people who go down this road never come back.
Because it leads to the morgue.
I will have you get right to work.
The work is nothing too complicated.
When the bodies come in, you remove their clothing and wipe them clean.
Then you look for anything that might identify them.
If no one comes to claim them,
we put them on the carriage to the graveyard.
Every day it is more of the same.
Damn you, you were laughing at me!
I bet you two are friends in bed, too!
You are joining giblets, are not ya?
For goodness' sake, not him again.
He is as low as they come, is not he?
Too stubborn to pop off, eh?
It is been a while, has not it, Dad?
Yes, dead bodies from all over London end up there.
I did not know so many people died every day.
They know about Miss Dorothy's situation,
yet they are making her spend time with that horrible father.
Wh-what tea would you like to have tonight?
And what brings you here, Young Lady?
Oh, you do not have to tell me if you do not want to.
This place is largely ignored by the rest of the world.
And that is exactly what some of us want.
My leg was ruined in the War.
And all my friends are gone.
I feel right at home working with the dead.
If we steal the cipher, then Dad will...
My luck is changing, I swear.
You want me to pay back what I owe, do not ya?
I am a lot of things, but I are not a liar.
Just taking a bit longer than planned, is all.
You still have work to do.
I am taking a break, Love.
By pure coincidence, she came to work with me just the other day.
A looker like you must have any number of men dying for your hand.
I want to earn my own money.
I would be up the creek if my future husband ended up like my dad.
What do you know about anything?!
It is true, is not it?!
There are plenty of people out who have gotten hurt and are still doing what they can!
You are just using your injury as an excuse to run away!
Well, you should listen to your daughter and get to work.
I did not lose my hand'because I wanted to!
Little brat are not lived half as long as I have!
She is got no idea how much I have... how much I have...!
You should be ashamed of yourself!
Taking your anger out on everything around you!
You are her father, are not you?
Then maybe you should start to act like it, Sir!
What did you say, you little brat?
You are an interesting little girl.
A-a friend of yours, is she?
We... we were just having a little laugh.
He used to be an expert steam engineer.
But he got hurt in an accident, and it changed him.
He hates everyone around him, envies them.
He blames all of his problems on everyone else.
Why are ya looking at me like that!
If you have something to say, then say it!
You think I am a laughingstock, too!
Why do not you run out on me like SHE did?!
He would beat me within an inch of my life, then he would always...
I could not take it anymore, so I ran away.
To what is now the Commonwealth.
The Revolution came that same day.
So you could never go back.
I figured I would never have to see him again.
Mum ran out on us both, so I am grateful that he did not abandon me, too, but...
Why are you telling me all this?
I thought spies did not reveal their histories.
That is definitely true of Ange.
I am weaker than she is.
Well, if that is how you are going to talk, Miss Dorothy,
this is not just a cover anymore... we are real friends now!
Did I say anything to imply that?
That you can change the world?
But even if you could become Queen...
I want to stop having to hide our relationship, Charlotte.
But we are not the only ones who feel this way.
So many people have been torn apart by that Wall.
One day, their voices will all come together.
And you are going to wait for it?
I have waited ten years already.
Besides, it will not be like those ten years anymore.
I cannot believe you are already drunk.
Brings back memories, do not it?
He will not be waking any time soon.
He must have some way to contact the Duke of Normandy.
It should be in here somewhere.
Like he has not a care in the world.
You know Mum would never come back here.
No, I would rather be drunk, thanks.
I am not interested in a walk down our rubbish memory lane.
A body's going to show up at the morgue.
One with a cross carved into the palm of his hand.
And there is a note hidden in his tooth.
What is the point of that?
The important thing is that if we take it to a certain person, we will be rich.
A cross on the palm of his hand.
When you find the body, you tell me straightaway.
We are currently searching for the body.
I have made arrangements at the morgue.
The man has debts to pay.
Those motivated by money are always the most predictable.
I will be getting the money soon, all of it!
Then I swear I will pay you back!
And you expect me to believe that?
If YOU cannot pay, maybe we will ask your daughter to get us the money.
She really is quite a beauty.
Say the word, and I could consider your loan repaid.
I bet it was just another drunken brawl anyway!
I am going to copy it.
We cannot just take it with us?
We do not want the Duke of Normandy to find out.
If I just had the money, I would kiss this place goodbye.
Ugh, do not get carried away.
Get away from me, you reek of booze.
You will be drinking with me tonight!
Wait for me at the pub on Ghost Street!
I am kissing this rubbish life goodbye!
I would not be here if I did not.
You need it, do not you?
So let us see a little more money in return, eh?
Dad told me to meet him there.
You patched things up with your father.
Oh, I do not know about that.
Goodness gracious, she came with a bonus!
I did not think he would give me TWO.
Oh, no, did not he tell you?
Your father owes me a lot of money.
She is a nice bit of skirt, too.
That will cover interest and then some.
It is only logical that the daughter would shoulder her father's debt, is not it?
Hate the fact that you had that louse for a father.
Wait for me at the pub on Ghost Street!
I am kissing this rubbish life goodbye!
You just have to face facts.
What is wrong with you, woman?!
Sorry, but I am beyond furious right now.
Get up and show her what for!
Why did I ever think SHE was a looker?
Y-you came here alone, so I assumed he would given his seal of approval!
I told him to give us his daughter to pay off his loan.
I am getting a lot of money soon!
I swear I will pay you back!
We hit him, we kicked him, but that is all he would say!
Took quite a lot of work getting this.
Searching corpses with my daughter, day in and day out.
That is why I want you to pay both of us.
I would not recommend getting too greedy.
I am going to buy her some clothes,
and we will walk around town together.
I will say, Look at that?
I never thought I would see her again, but there she was.
So we need some funds to start over.
I am going to say goodbye to this rubbish life,
and turn over a new leaf!
I will put an end to this rubbish life of yours.
There are not any other good pubs in the area.
And they serve a pretty decent stout, if nothing else.
I will excuse myself as soon as your father gets here.
He is not exactly the type to keep his promises.
But he really does care about you.
If he had been even a little more decent a human being, I would not have run away.
And you would not have become a spy?
I might be hawking bread for a baker somewhere.
Then I have your father to thank that I got to meet you, Miss Dorothy.
Even if he is the weakest, most worthless father of all time.
He was a good dad, back when he was still an engineer.
He used to sing me to sleep.
Dad and I both loved that song.
On just a dazzling summer's night
On just a dazzling summer's night
On just a dazzling summer's night
On just a dazzling summer's night
We dance the light steps of a merry melody
So on nights when the moon is beautiful, remember
Although we are so far apart now
You are dearer to me than anything in the world
You are dearer to me than anything in the world
You are dearer to me than anything in the world
You are dearer to me than anything in the world
